-- Knicks Beat Wizards for 3rd Straight Win, Nets Lose to Mavericks
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2013-03-02T05:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-02/knicks-beat-wizards-for-3rd-straight-win-nets-lose-to-mavericks.html
Carmelo Anthony scored 30 points to
lead the New York Knicks to a 96-88 victory over the Washington
Wizards and their third straight win in the National Basketball
Association.  The Knicks (35-20) lead the Eastern Conference’s five-team
Atlantic Division, three games ahead of the Brooklyn Nets
(34-25), who lost 98-90 to the Dallas Mavericks.  Raymond Felton  had 23 points and J.R. Smith came off the
bench to tally 13 points and 12 rebounds last night at the
Verizon Center in Washington.  Bradley Beal scored 29 points for the Wizards, while  John Wall  contributed 16 and reserve Trevor Ariza added 15.  The Wizards (18-39) are third in the conference’s five-team
Southeast Division, 24 1/2 games behind the Miami Heat.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
